lopment, but jurisdictions have discretion over man‚Ä¶","‚Ä¶cost factors, and priorities. Oregon‚Äôs SDC Act and the broader legal context provide guardrails to ensure SDCs recover an equitable share of costs of capacity, while also providing flexibility to tailor the approach to community values and local circums‚Ä¶ | ‚Ä¶contributions to growth- related costs, and they can support housing production by funding capital projects needed for growth. However, the equity implications of relying on SDCs to fund eligible infrastructure projects are mixed. Residential SDCs can be regressive, with higher impacts‚Ä¶"
